    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-19T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-19T23:00:00-05:00" n="524"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d524">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13412: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-20T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 20, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 20—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. Shanghai’s 164 [<hi rend="italic">165</hi>], March 19, 4 p.m. Embassy is
                    informing Foreign Office and requesting that military authorities be directed to
                    afford adequate protection to Americans at Hungtung. Shanghai informed of action
                    taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
